{
  "stem": "8786.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But sometimes, you have to make a step.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I did not have-- I did not have any strength.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He-- I ask him to help, help me up-- the conductor, conductor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I came, too, with a friend of mine, with this same Mr.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Krakowich, who was so painfully mourning after his brother-- the same car, Mr.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Krakowich.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We came down to, to Pressburg, Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That's the capital of Slovakia today, a old famous town, a holy town where our greatest rabbis were establishing, actually, the, the Jewish tradition for the whole Hungarian country-- Pressburg, Bratislava-- famous, beautiful town.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we stayed there not more than about 24 hours and tried to get a train further.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We went down to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Budapest is also the first time I was there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He knew, already, the town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they took us into the so-called [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] big office of the-- of the-- of the-- of the-- of the Holocaust survivors.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you see over there, hundreds and hundreds of people with lists.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everybody looking for somebody.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody's looking for relatives, for friends, looking-- maybe you know where my brother is.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Did you see my father?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Did you see my sisters?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the first time-- I'll never forget that-- I come-- I came down to, to, to Pressburg.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At the station, I met my former teacher, a lady, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Charlotte Brown.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were very close with the family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she didn't see no man in the whole year, because the-- all these girls-- all the ladies were separated.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The men were separated from the ladies.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She saw me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she hugged me and jumped on my-- like, like a mother finds a child.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's how she, she was-- so happy was she to find me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was Charlotte Brown.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
